        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 12:29PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1229 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cripple Creek, or 21 miles west of Colorado Springs, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Woodland Park, Cripple Creek, Green Mountain Falls, Divide, and Pikes
Peak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
